@superatomic would you mind rebasing
> But it would be strange to end up with a `get_config` that has a callback parameter for fully evaluated configurations and a `get_configs` that returns partially evaluated configurations.

@mfussenegger  We can add a `on_config` param to this `get_configs` later (i.e. we don't need the singular `get_config`).

The partially evaluated situation is unfortunate but it's something we can document and the user can choose whether they care. The current situation is that people have to either reach into the internals or just are totally blocked.
